# Transport-layer security headers for nomad.md
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This file is consumed by Netlify, Cloudflare Pages, and (with translation)
# any static host that supports the `_headers` format. GitHub Pages does not
# honour `_headers`; deploy the equivalent via a `<meta http-equiv>` block in
# `src/app.html` (we ship a `frame-ancestors` fallback there) and via the
# static-host-specific config (e.g. `_redirects` for SPA fallback).
#
# Policy choices:
#  - `default-src 'self'` — strict default; only same-origin by default.
#  - `script-src 'self'` — no inline scripts, no eval. The Svelte 5 / Vite
#    production build does not inject inline scripts at the time of writing;
#    if a future change needs one, add its SHA-256 here (not 'unsafe-inline').
#  - `style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'` — Tailwind 4 + Svelte's component-
#    scoped styles rely on inline `style="..."` for a few transitions. The
#    long-term goal is hashed nonces (see SECURITY.md); `unsafe-inline` is
#    documented as a temporary relaxation.
#  - `img-src 'self' data: blob:` — Markdown rendering and inline image
#    previews.
#  - `connect-src 'self' https://cors.isomorphic-git.org` — Remote Mode's
#    CORS proxy. `self` is required for SvelteKit's data fetching (in our
#    build, no fetches run on this host, but the directive is harmless and
#    future-proof).
#  - `object-src 'none'` — defence-in-depth against <object> / <embed>.
#  - `base-uri 'self'` — no <base> injection.
#  - `frame-ancestors 'none'` — clickjacking defence (the `<meta>` fallback
#    in app.html is the case the host strips headers).
#  - `form-action 'self'` — only same-origin form submissions.
#  - `require-trusted-types-for 'script'` — opt the app into Trusted Types;
#    the renderer + DOMPurify policy (`'nomad-md'`) is the documented sink.
#
# Strict-Transport-Security: enables HTTPS-only mode for 2 years plus
# subdomains. The `preload` directive is only effective after submission to
# the HSTS preload list; ships commented out by default.
# Referrer-Policy: no-referrer — the URL bar never leaks the current path.
# Permissions-Policy: every common sensor / API denied by default.
# Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin — process isolation.
# Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp — required for SharedArrayBuffer
# (the jsdom renderer test path relies on it) and isolates the page.
# X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff — prevents MIME-type sniffing.

/
	Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains
	X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
	Referrer-Policy: no-referrer
	Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), interest-cohort=(), payment=(), usb=(), serial=(), bluetooth=(), midi=()
	Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
	Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp
	Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: same-origin
	Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data: blob:; font-src 'self'; connect-src 'self' https://cors.isomorphic-git.org; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; form-action 'self'; require-trusted-types-for 'script'; trusted-types nomad-md dompurify default

/_app/immutable/*
	Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
